Mail and Passenger Steamships. Regular Service fortnightly from HAMBURG;
                        weekly from ANTWERP; every 2 weeks from BORDEAUX direct to ALEXANDRIA;
                        homewards every 2 weeks from ALEXANDRIA for ROTTERDAM and HAMBURG. Goods
                        forwarded at through-rates from all German Railway Stations on direct Bills
                        of Lading to ALEXANDRIA, CAIRO, SYRIA, etc.

Regarding the letter signed "truly yonre X" iu your paper of 26th ulto (in
                        which he writes of the "English Residents In Alexandria") I very much doubt
                        if Lord Cromer was in any way responsible for the abolition of the (supreme)
                        British (Consular) Court at Alexandria. Perhaps X can prove his statement :
                        if not, I think that his letter is to say the least of it ungenerons. I am,
                        etc. J. MURRAY. Midlothian N.B. August 2.
